{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_evans_ver01/data/sn86063730/00332893786/1930111301/0225.xml":{"full_text":"SWANIANS OF\n12 CITIES MEET\n,N(P\nfjarlingen Surprises Sister\n1 City of San Benito\nWith Program\nA\n(Special to The Herald)\n.SAN BENITO, Nov. 13\u2014 Hands\ntf friendship were extended across\nIBS Arroyo Colorado Wednesday as\n\u00aewanians of the twin cities Har\nUjBgen and San Benito, met to\n\u25a0fther at the Stonewall Jackson\nSlOtrt and heard Inspiring Armistice\nDay talks from Rev. L. A Boons.\n\u25a0Ww pastor of the Methodist church\nat Harlingen and J. P. Rodgers,\nDOBtmaster th^rp\n|When San Benito Kiwanians\ndyed at the hotel they discovered,\n%o their surprise, visitors seated on\n\u25a0ttterna&e chairs at the luncheon\nftble. Probably nonplussed by the\npresence of 40 visiting Kiwanians.\nthey were late in coming in.\nPresident W. M. Driskell of the\nHarlingen club. who presided,\npromptly made them spin their\nown tardy wheel to determine\nttieir punishment. Each had to pay\na small fine.\n.The Rev. Mr. Boone, at one time j\nChaplain for the Texas depart- j\nBlent of the American Legion.\nmade an Armistice Day talk in\nwhich he stressed man power as\n\u2022pposed to man\u2019s power or the\nspiritual force as opposed to com\nmercial gain. He pointed out that\n\u2022very colony planted on American\nshores for commercial gain failed\nbut that those which rallied on\naims more worthy survived. Not\n\u25a0o much reliance should be Placed\n\u2022n machinery and other evidence\ntlf man\u2019s power but more on such\nnoble qualities as go towards mak\nnte manpower, he .said.\nRodgers dwelled on the\ngrowth of communism and other\nthrees destructive to government,\n.pointing out that they were op\nposed to the principles for which\n\u2018America fought during the World\nr\nThe program was in charge of\nD W. Dav of Harlingen who re\ntired to the mixups caused by the\n'fact that there was a D W Day\n,'Sn San Benito, also a Klw&nlan.\n\u2022Mr. Rodgers similarly made refer\nence to R. W. Nelson of Harlingen\n\u2022#lth whom he Is often confusea\nbecause of physical resemblances.\nMrs. Jack Carev of Harlingen\nentertained the joint meeting with\nfeveral vocal solos, being ac\ncompanied by Mrs S R Jennings\nFour of the aviators present for\nthe San Benito airport celebration\n*jjpere Introduced as guests.\nHomer Maxwell won the Har\n*bngen attendance pri*e donated by\nDr. Driskell.\nAfc _________\n^.Hydrogen, which Is an element,\nit the lightest substance known to\n\u2022dlence. Its specific gravity, com\npared with air. Is 0W5.\nr 1 1 1\nCHEVROLET DISPLAYS NEW CAR\nNew 1931 Chevrolet Six Sport Roadster {with rumble seat)\nChevrolet* new car for 1931, priced substantially below current levels, is on display throughout the\nnation. The new car boasts a two-inch increase in wheelbase, larger and roomier bodies by Fisher with\nmohair or broadcloth as optional trimming, and scores of refinements in appearance and performance\ndespite the new prices which bring the level for -he 1931 car to a far lower figure than any Chevrolet,\nfour or six, has ever sold. Dealers throughout the United States put the new models on exhibition\nnearly two months in advance of the customary date for the showing of the annual new car. This move\nin advancing the announcement date, it was felt by Chevrolet officials, would render a distinct contribu\ntion to the cause of general business revival by Insuring extraordinary activity during two normally\ndull business months for the 200,000 people throughout the United States who depend directly upon\nChevrolet for their livelihood.\nRUBIO FACES\n(Continued From Page One\u00bb\ntion and highway construction In\n1031 is the largest in the history\nof Mexico. An educated man him\nself. the president feels that edu\ncation and ample communication\nfacilities are vitally necessary for\nthe development of his country.\nDuring recent months he has per\nsonally authored several measures\ndesigned to make educational fa\ncilities more accessible to his coun\ntrymen.\nEarly completion of the vast\nhighway construction program,\nwhich is being pushed by Minister\nof Communication Oeneral Juan\nAndreu Almazan, has a two-fold\npurpose in the president's recon\nstruction program. Besides offering*!\nMexicans an opportunity to see\ntheir own country and thus elimi\nnate provincialism, the highways\nwill create a highly profitable\nsource of revenue for the govern\nment and ettirens through the in\nflux of tourists.\nAfter submitting the budget for\nnext year to congress, President\nOrtis Rubio sent to congress a\nmessage, later widely acclaimed by\nthe Mexican press, in which he out\nlined his program for the ambitious\ncampaign, which observers say will\nbe the severest test of his ability\nto lead his country.\nInvestments Favored\n\"The time has arrived to end\nany movements intended to aggra\nvate or prevent relief to the pres\nent critical condition,\u201d the presi\ndent said \"It is also time for con\ngress to legislate laws establishing\norganic equilibrium between capi\ntal and labor.\"\nThis last remark attracted .\u2022ten'\ntlon not only in Industrial and la\nbor headquarters of Mexico but in\nthe United States where manv in\nvestors have delayed their entry\ninto Mexico until the adoption of\nequitable labor laws.\n\"We must create a state of con\nfidence to favor investments,\u201d he\ncontinued. \"We realise that this\nrequires settlement of two major\nproblems. They are the agrarian\nand labor questions, both of which\nconstitute the basis of the revolu\ntionary program.\u201d\nCongress already is studying\ntentative changes in the labor\nlaws. A few hours after his mes\nsage was delivered. President Ortiz\nRubio sent to congress an amend\nment to the agrarian laws, making\nseveral basic changes in their\npresent operation.\nLaws Revised?\nThe p re s i d e n t\u2019s amendment\nwould exclude from the presmt\nagragrian laws the provision al\nlowing for the taking over for dis\ntribution to peasants lands In pro\nduction of fruit, dairy, sugar,\nvegetable or cattle. Many land\nowners have hesitated to operate\ntheir haciendas for fear of having\n666\nis a doctor's Prescription for\nColds and Headaches\nIt is the most speedy remedy known\n666 also in Tablets\nthem taken over and distributed\nto peasants. The amendment also\nrejects the demand of villages for\nenlargement of their communal\nlands unless they have money on\nhand to pay the landowners. At\npresent land seized paid for In\nfederal agragrian bonds which are\ncashable at about 16 per cent of\ntheir face value.\nThe amendment also would give\nhacienda owners the right to em\nploy large numbers of peons with\nout being under obligation to give\nthe peons land. It has been the\npractice in the past for peons to\nform a village on the \u2019\u2019.acienda\nemploying them and demand, and\nreceive, communal lands at the\nexpense of the landowner.\n\"It is my determination to take\nwhatever steps are necessary to\nplace the finances of Mexico on a\nsound basis, to carry out both the\ninternal and exterior obligations,\nand to award full protection to\nboth capital and labor,\u201d the presid\nent further declared\nConfidence Gained\nAlthough the optimism voiced\nEndorsed By\nBeautiful Women\nBeauties who guard their com\nplexions use MELLO-GLO Face\nPowder only. Famous for purity\u2014\nits coloring matter is approved by\nthe Government The rero\u00ab\n'ooks pasty or flaky. It spreads\nmore smoothly and p.odu t\nyouthful bloom. Made by a .ie\\v\nFrench process. MELLO-GLO Face\nPowder stays on longer Cisneros\nDrue Stores.\nAtwatem Kewt\nKADI3\nYour choice today!\nYour pride in\nyears to come\nthe radio with the GOLDEN VOICE\nXo MOST CLEAR-THINKING PEOPLE the\nchoke of a radio k simple. It k an investment in hap\npiness\u2014not for today alone, but for yean to come.\nClear reasoning leads directly to Atwater Kent\u2014\nwith eight years of leadership behind it\u2